SummaryTextDescription: The expansive property is 800 sqm and has been beautifully designed throughout with bespoke interiors and fittings. The lift opens directly onto a private lobby with Deco details, which is only the prologue to the rest of this magnificent property. A set of splendid, bespoke walnut burr doors lead into a grand and dramatic 3-m high ceiling reception room with a white baby grand piano. The windows and French windows all around this room grant an extraordinary view of the Park and open onto a vast decked roof terrace. This luxury apartment occupies the 6th floor of a historical building and can accommodate up to 12 guests in 6 elegant en suite bedrooms, each of them with its unique style. The property offers hydrotherapy Jacuzzi, a striking fitness room with state-of-the-art Technogym equipment and a Kinesis Personal Trainer with a custom designed massage room.

Descriptions.Text: This magnificent new residence of grand proportions extends to about 11,000 sq ft. The accommodation is cleverly arranged over 4 floors and from the grand reception hall with a lift serving 3 floors and sweeping staircase to the stylish leisure complex this superb property simply exudes style and quality. State of the art facilities can also be found throughout including under floor, mood lighting and an integrated sound system. The reception rooms are spacious and well arranged for entertaining on a grand scale as well as being equally well suited for family living.Approached via carriage driveway; grand entrance hall, drawing room, dining room, family room, sitting room, bespoke kitchen/breakfast room, utility room, first floor atrium living area, 4 bedroom suites, 3/4 further bedrooms, shower room, lower ground floor leisure complex with swimming pool, gym, steam room and sauna, lift to 3 floors. Externally offering; landscaped gardens, garage and ample off street parking.

SummaryTextDescription: One of the most beautiful estates in England, particularly so in the North West. Indeed the exquisitely beautiful Palladian house is widely regarded as the most important country house built in the 20th century in England.The style of the house is based on Palladio's Villa Capra, known as The Rotunda, at Vicenza, the best known English versions of which, both 18th century, are Mereworth Castle in Kent and Chiswick House in London.Sits in a wonderfully commanding position with fabulous vistas in every direction over the Estate. In addition to the main house is the Tenants' Hall, which provides additional guest accommodation, and private gardens and grounds extending to about 12 acres.These gardens are exquisitely beautiful with a series of lakes as the centrepiece, which are in impeccable condition. There is also a swimming pool, tennis court and stable block.In addition to the principal house and Tenants' Hall there is a Grade II secondary house, The Cave, together with 5 further houses and cottages.

SummaryTextDescription: This spacious lateral three double bedroom apartment is located on the second floor of an attractive and well-maintained period building and benefits from a lift and porter. The building itself is stucco fronted and upon entering there is a well-presented lobby area with porters desk and access to the lift. On entering the apartment there is a spacious and welcoming hallway, with double doors leading to the 35 foot reception room and through to the well-appointed, modern Kitchen. Both rooms are flooded with natural light and benefit from elevated views. The vast main reception room easily accommodates a large formal dining area as well as a separate sitting area. Off the reception room is a good-sized informal sitting room / study with its own balcony. The master bedroom is located to the rear of the building and has its own balcony with fully folding doors as well as a dressing area and bathroom with freestanding bath tub and separate glass shower cubicle. There are two further good-sized double bedrooms with en suite bathrooms and a guest WC that is also fitted with a shower cubicle.

SummaryTextDescription: A substantial and extremely well appointed detached residence set on a generous plot on one of Loughton's premier roads. The spacious internal accommodation which is arranged over two levels includes oak panelling and parque flooring. The remainder of the interior comprises an entrance hall leading to the fabulous ground floor rooms including a living room, a study and a formal dining room. The outstanding kitchen/breakfast room has a comprehensive range of quality fitted units. Double doors lead onto the beautiful landscaped garden. There is also a useful utility room with wc. The first floor provides five double bedrooms, two with en suite facilities, and a further family bathroom. The delightful garden measures approx. 190' x 78' has been carefully landscaped to give a wide lawn with mature borders and shrubs. There is a fantastic swimming pool making the garden a wonderful family area. SummaryTextDescription: Set on a generous plot with further potential to extend, subject to the usual consents, is this spacious five bedroom, four reception room detached family home. The property has a 14ft master bedroom with en-suite and views over London towards Canary Wharf. There is a further en-suite to the second bedroom, ground floor cloakroom, a wonderful 15ft orangery and a 17ft kitchen/breakfast room. The rear garden measures 63ft x 70ft and there is a double garage with parking also to the front. The Summit is a cul-de-sac located opposite Epping Forest and also within the Staples Road school catchment.
